<content type="str">ï»¿ MANAMA: Communication and collaboration challenges of the modern working environment was the theme of an information technology (IT) workshop hosted by Hilal Computers. Twenty senior IT professionals from an array of different industries and sectors in Bahrain took part in the Cisco Collaboration Roundtable at the Four Seasons Hotel Bahrain Bay, where representatives from the global technology firm showcased the latest developments and innovations in the communications, messaging and video conference solutions arena. Participants discussed opportunities and difficulties arising from changes taking place in the modern working environment. &quot;Static teams working from fixed offices often working alone has become a thing of the past,&quot; said Hilal Computers Network operations manager Sachin Dev. &quot;The modern information worker needs access from anywhere, anytime using any device in order to communicate and collaborate with teams that now include employees, partners and customers in a single seamless environment.&quot;Hilal Computers is a Premier Certified Cisco partner for infrastructure and networking services, which includes, but is not limited to, storage and virtualisation; disaster recovery/business continuity; big data solutions; unified communications; routing solutions and network performance analysis. The company has consistently demonstrated excellence in setting and managing customer expectations, proactively communicating with customers, and defining organisational goals. Following the success of the latest Cisco Collaboration Roundtable, Hilal Computers plans to host a collaborative workshop for industry professionals relating to Cisco security solutions and its range of cybersecurity products, from advanced malware protection and cloud security to next-generation firewalls. (c) 2017 2016 Al Hilal Publishing and Marketing Group Provided by SyndiGate Media Inc. (Syndigate.info)., source Middle East &amp; North African Newsp